  <title>Topic Tree documents <lnpid>id-UK13-30024</lnpid></title>
  <body>
    <p><b>Topic Tree documents</b> are differentiated from <xref href="pods.dita">POD
        documents</xref> by having <sourcexml>comm:body/level/@leveltype="practicearea"</sourcexml>.
      Topic Tree documents will also have a <sourcexml>docinfo:selector</sourcexml> that contains
      only the exact text "LandingPages_TopicTree". Any landing page source document with this
      mark-up should <b><u>not</u></b> be converted using the instructions in this document. </p>
    <p><b>As of July 2016, topic tree documents will be converted from Rosetta mark-up to SKOS
        format XML by a separate conversion running as XSLT on the ICCE platform.</b></p>    
    <note>The above mark-up indicates what <b><u>differentiates</u></b> landing pages that are Topic Tree
      documents from landing pages that are POD documents. <b><u>Both</u></b> POD documents
      <b><u>and</u></b> Topic Tree documents will have a
      <sourcexml>docinfo:selector</sourcexml> that <b><u>starts</u></b> with the exact text
      "LandingPages_" (including the underscore), as described at the <xref href="body.dita">beginning of this Body section</xref>.</note>    
    <section>
      <title>Source XML showing indication of a Topic Tree document that should not be converted with this instructions</title>
      <codeblock>

&lt;COMMENTARYDOC ...&gt;
  &lt;docinfo ...&gt;
    &lt;!-- ... --&gt;
    &lt;docinfo:doc-id&gt;LandingPages_TopicTree&lt;/docinfo:doc-id&gt;
    &lt;!-- ... --&gt;
  &lt;/docinfo&gt;
  &lt;comm:body&gt;
    &lt;level leveltype="practicearea"&gt;
    &lt;!-- ... --&gt;

      </codeblock>
    </section>
